
Read a text file and print the following statistics on the screen as well to an output file:
• the size of the file in bytes
• number of times the search-string specified in the second argument appeared in the file

Use make to generate executable file "count".
 
Type in "./count <input-filename> <search-string> <output-filename>". 
If search-string contains blank space, make sure the search-string surrounded by double-quotes.
